<HTML>
  <HEAD>
    <TITLE>Hello.</TITLE>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <STYLE>
      .header {
	  font-size:130%;
	  font-weight: bold;
      }
      @media screen and (min-width:0px) and (max-width:440px) {
	  .hide-mobile {
	      display:none !important;
	  }
	  .photostream img {
	      height: 100px;
	      width: auto;
	  }
      }
      @media screen and (min-width:401px) {
      }
      .row {
	  display: flex;
	  flex-direction: row;
	  flex-wrap: wrap;
	  width: 100%;
      }
      .column {
	  display: flex;
	  flex-direction: column;
	  flex-basis: 100%;
	  flex: 1;
      }
      .photostream {
	  width: 50%;
      }

      UL {
	  display: flex;
          flex-wrap: wrap;
	  list-style-type: none;
	  margin: 0;
	  padding: 0;
	  overflow: hidden;
      }
      LI {
	  padding: 1px 0px 0px 1px;
	  flex-grow:1;
      }
      LI:last-child {
	  flex-grow: 10;
      }                                                                                                                                             
      .photostream img {
	  max-height: 100%;
	  min-width: 100%;
	  object-fit: cover;
	  vertical-align: bottom;
      }  
      .padded {
	  padding: 10px;
      }
      
    </STYLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY style="padding:0px; margin:0px;">
    <DIV class="row">
      <DIV class="photostream">
	<A class=header HREF="photostream/">
	  <UL>
	    {% for photo in photos %}
	    <LI><IMG SRC="photostream/thumbnails/{{ photo.name }}.jpg" loading="lazy" class="galthumb" width="{{ photo.width}}" height="{{ photo.height }}" /></LI>
	    {% endfor %}
	    <LI></LI>
	  </UL>
	</A>
      </DIV>
      <DIV class="column">
	<DIV class="padded">
	  <SPAN class=header>Photos.</SPAN><BR/>
	  I still write HTML like it's 1999. I may try to "learn" things as I do this, like how the modern web works.<BR/>
	  <A HREF="/2019_book_photos/">2019 book photos</A><BR/>
	  <A HREF="/2018_book_photos/">2018 book photos</A><BR/>
	  <A HREF="/2017_book_photos/">2017 book photos</A><BR/>
	  <A HREF="/2016_book_photos/">2016 book photos</A><BR/>
	  <A HREF="/2015_book_photos/">2015 book photos</A><BR/>
	</DIV>

	<DIV style="background-color:#eee; text-align:left;" class="padded">
	  <SPAN class=header>Keepsakes.</SPAN><BR/>
	  <A HREF="/static/ethan_santa_letter.html">ethan's santa letter</A><br/>
	  <A HREF="/static/to_my_unborn_child.html">to my unborn child</A>
	</DIV>

	<DIV class="padded">
	  <SPAN class=header>Blog.</SPAN><BR/>
	  <A HREF="/static/blog.html">Blog</A>
	</DIV>
      </DIV>

      <DIV class="column hide-mobile">
	<DIV class="padded">
	  <SPAN class=header>Books.</SPAN><BR/>
	  PDF book links. There are VERY LARGE, don't download them on a phone.<br/>
	  <A HREF="/static/pdfs/2019_book.pdf">2019 book PDF version</A><BR/>
	  <A HREF="/static/pdfs/2018_book.pdf">2018 book PDF version</A><BR/>
	  <A HREF="/static/pdfs/2017_book.pdf">2017 book PDF version</A><BR/>
	  <A HREF="/static/pdfs/2016_book.pdf">2016 book PDF version</A><BR/>
	</DIV>

	<DIV class="padded">
	  <SPAN class=header>New.</SPAN><BR/>  I dramatically changed
	  the Photostream layout to remove the use of Javascript,
	  which I hate. I added a Photostream to the home page.
	</DIV>
      </DIV>
    </DIV>
  </BODY>
</HTML>
